# Phase 4 PoC — SHACL parallel of PageObjectivesValidator
#
# Source: plans/phase-4-validators-to-shacl.md (sub-plan of
# plans/rdf-shacl-enrichment-2026-04-26.md). This file expresses the
# structural part of the page_objectives gate in SHACL Core: every
# Courseforge CourseModule (each generated week_*.html page) must declare
# at least one learning objective via schema:teaches.
#
# Wired as a parallel `page_objectives_shacl` gate at:
#   - course_generation.packaging
#   - textbook_to_course.packaging
# Severity is `warning` so the SHACL gate is INFORMATIONAL during the
# PoC window — the existing Python gate at the same phase remains
# authoritative. See sub-plan §8.
#
# Namespaces are canonical (sub-plan §10): no new IRI scheme is minted.
# Target: ed4all:CourseModule (Wave 62 @context aliases "@type":
# "CourseModule" -> ed4all:CourseModule). Path: schema:teaches (the
# Wave 62 @context aliases the "learningObjectives" JSON key onto
# schema:teaches with @container:@set). Constraint: sh:minCount 1.
#
# Result message (sh:message at the SHAPE level — pyshacl copies onto
# every produced sh:resultMessage) follows Q43 authoring rules:
#   - domain-language constraint name
#   - expected vs found
#   - actionable suggestion
#   - stable code prefix (PO-001) for downstream tooling routing.
#
# Discrepancy with the Python gate (sub-plan §9.2): the Python validator
# treats `learningObjectives: []` as pass (no LO-specificity violation
# in an empty allowed-set). The SHACL shape REJECTS empty-LO pages —
# this is richer-diagnostics-for-free, the LO-fanout failure mode the
# Python gate was meant to catch but currently silently allows.

@prefix sh:       <http://www.w3.org/ns/shacl#> .
@prefix rdfs:     <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix schema:   <http://schema.org/> .
@prefix ed4all:   <https://ed4all.dev/ns/courseforge/v1#> .
@prefix cfshapes: <https://ed4all.dev/ns/courseforge/v1/shapes#> .

cfshapes:PageObjectivesMinCountShape
  a sh:NodeShape ;
  sh:targetClass ed4all:CourseModule ;
  rdfs:label "Page Objectives Min-Count Shape (Phase 4 PoC)" ;
  rdfs:comment "Phase 4 PoC of plans/rdf-shacl-enrichment-2026-04-26.md. Parallel of PageObjectivesValidator's structural per-page LO presence check. Each ed4all:CourseModule (one per generated HTML page) must declare at least one learning objective. Critical-severity violation in shape land; surfaced as a `warning` gate during the PoC so the existing Python gate stays authoritative." ;

  sh:property [
    sh:path schema:teaches ;
    sh:minCount 1 ;
    sh:severity sh:Violation ;
    sh:message "PO-001: every CourseModule must declare at least one learning objective via schema:teaches (expected at least 1, found 0). Add a learningObjectives entry referencing a canonical TO-NN or CO-NN ID for this page's week. See plans/phase-4-validators-to-shacl.md." ;
  ] .
